{
  "texts": [
    "A number of DL studies have has employed DL to classify fossils from across a broad range of evolutionary clades (refer to Table 5).",
    "Liu et al. (2023) present a DL framework for the taxonomic identification of fossils from across the tree of life.",
    "An Inception-ResNet-V2 hybrid model is fine-tuned, producing noteworthy accuracy.",
    "Misidentification does occur in this study, and is particularly prominent for sponges, bryozoans, and trace fossils, challenges arising from the high morphological disparity of fossils included in the study, and the learning class characteristics in training, namely image quality, low data volume, and other factors.",
    "Moreover, the groups with low identification performance were often confused with one another, suggesting the need for improving discriminative features in the model."
  ]
}